; Negation under a same-batch add+remove flap of the negated fact. One
; batch both adds and removes blocker(3) (never previously present), and a
; later batch both adds and removes blocker(2) (already present). Ingest
; netting would leave the database unchanged in both cases; today's engine
; dequeues adds and removes in an internal order
; (docs/proposals/StackSafeNegation.md, Open Question 3), and this case
; pins that order-dependent outcome as the baseline: the absent-fact flap
; nets to nothing, but for the present fact the removal wins and
; blocker(2) ends absent (item 2 becomes visible).
#message blocker(i32 X) @differential.
#message item(i32 X).

#local blocked(i32 X).
#local stored(i32 X).

#query visible(free i32 X).

blocked(X) : blocker(X).
stored(X) : item(X).

visible(X) : stored(X), !blocked(X).
